Patch Set 2: Sanity-Review+1

Patch Set 2:

Any comments?

Patch Set 2:

Morten can you as our "high dpi expert" have a look please?

Patch Set 2:

I think this patch is mainly focus on how we calculate the frame margin, it has little to do with high dpi stuff.

Patch Set 2:

The calculation expression "resize border thickness = size frame width (x/y) + padded border width" is verified in many famous open source projects, such as Chromium, Mozilla Firefox, Windows Terminal and etc. It has been there for many years, running normally on numerous PCs, so I think it's safe for Qt to adopt this. And according to my test, the calculated of that expression value is correct on various DPIs.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

Looks good to me.

Patch Set 1:

https://eel.is/c++draft/dcl.attr.unused#2 says clearly that [[maybe_unused]] can be applied there. And I'm positive it's there because otherwise Clang complains about the unused member.

This is a GCC bug: https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=92562

I'd suggest to introduce a Q_UNUSED_DATA_MEMBER or somesuch that expands to [[maybe_unused]] on non-GCC, and nothing on GCC.
